
***** Ypos: getting the Y coordinates *****

token(s):
T_Ypos Ypos

rule(s):
image -> T_Ypos( VAR_IMAGE )

description:
Creates an new USHORT image that contains
the Y coordinates of the given image.
This can be very useful for arithmetic
operations on images.

Example(s):
- Putting the image borders in Y coordinates at 0:

y = Ypos(i)
i = i*(y>2)*(y<i.ty-3)

See Also:
	Xpos, Zpos


